snippet.textDisplay: The quarantine is only to prevent the spread at a large scale. It's really only to not overwhelm hospitals. You will be exposed at one point. The healthier population isnt going to be that affected. But the elderly, pregnant, youth(under the age of 5 I think), and auto immune compromised. For stages most the population won't even need hospitalization, some will need clinical check-ups, and the rest might need intense ICU care. Quarantine is not to prevent you from getting it at all. It is only to spread it out in case you do need hospital care. The only worry to have is if it mutates again. We have known of the coronavirus since (like) the 60s. But it has mutated like any other illness. But it's discovery was not in anyway harmless. It over time has gotten to be something to worry about (obviously) BUT the only really concerning part is it mutates TO FAST causing any research to relapse and go back to square one.

snippet.textDisplay: I work for a children's theatre in Birmingham, Alabama and we have had to cancel our upcoming shows due to COVID19. Since most of our income is from school groups coming to see shows as field trips, we're definitely struggling. It would mean so much if you guys considered us as a charity to donate to. We have a GoFundMe up and are trying to raise around $20,000 to be able to stay in operation and open back up in time for Summer workshops and camps. This theatre means so much to me and many other people in my city. Kids are introduced to a style of art, our workshops and classes are meant to help teach skills and techniques to kids who want to be on stage. We focus on build self-esteem, confidence, and making sure that kids leave the building inspired and encouraged to express themselves (even if it's not in a theatre). So I'm taking the chance of asking for the help of Unnas Annus, I'm a huge fan and love watching you guys. Thank you to anyone who read this! Stay healthy and safe!💛
